UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1386418122000581
KW  - Distraction
KW  - Limited attention
KW  - Market quality
AB  - This study examines the effects of intra-day anticipated distraction events on market quality. This is achieved by exploiting the quasi-random nature by which FIFA World Cup football matches overlap with the domestic trading hours of participating countries. Utilizing stock market data from 24 countries and a sample of 95 football matches, I find that match days exhibit pre-match increases to trading volume and contemporaneous declines to trading activity. Market volatility follows a similar trend. Realized spreads are increased during matches. Match time is associated with increased price efficiency, suggesting reduced noise trading.
