KW  - Fixed-income securities
KW  - Bonds
KW  - Exchange-traded funds
KW  - Information
KW  - JEL classification: G0
KW  - G12
KW  - G23
AB  - We analyze the relation between ETF ownership and firm-specific information in corporate bond returns. ETF ownership appears to weaken bond price informativeness by altering the flow of firm-specific information to bonds. Bonds with low (high) ETF ownership are sensitive (insensitive) to the same information as equity. Using earnings announcements, we show that bonds with low ETF ownership react to earnings news, but bonds with high levels do not. Moreover, we find a positive association between investment-grade bond return comovement with the market and ETF ownership, implying that return variation is less attributable to firm-level information as ETF ownership increases.
